message.content:
Below is one reasonable “best‐fit” reading of the scene that uses only the block‐orientations shown in the dictionary (no additional rotations).  First comes a careful inventory of what is in the Target Image, then which Dictionary blocks match, and finally a plausible step‐by‐step build order.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
1)  DESCRIPTION OF THE TARGET STRUCTURE
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
•  Overall there are two separate sub‐structures:

  A)  LEFT “TOWER” SUB‐STRUCTURE
     –  Base/Column:  Two orange cylinders stacked vertically, forming a tall column.  
     –  Top “Roof”:  An orange wedge‐shaped block capping the column.  
     –  Mid‐Level Platform:  Two yellow rectangular blocks arranged horizontally around the mid‐height of the column.  One extends far enough to hold a blue cube; the other supports a red arch.  
     –  Red Arch + Blue Cube:  At that same mid‐level, a single red arch sits over the column, and a blue cube is perched out front.

  B)  RIGHT “H‐SHAPED” SUB‐STRUCTURE
     –  Four Red Arches:  Two arches form the “legs” on the bottom layer; two more arches sit on top.  
     –  Yellow Cross‐Bar:  Spanning the middle (left‐to‐right) between the two pairs of arches is a horizontal “band” of two yellow rectangular blocks.

•  Layer Count (conceptually):
  –  The left tower has three main vertical layers:
       1) The two stacked cylinders (base),
       2) The mid‐platform of yellow blocks + arch + cube,
       3) The orange wedge on top.
  –  The right “H” has two main layers:
       1) Bottom pair of red arches,
       2) Middle yellow cross‐bar + top arches.

•  Total Block Count (as interpreted here):
  –  Left Tower:  2 orange cylinders, 1 orange wedge, 1 red arch, 2 yellow rectangular blocks, 1 blue cube.
  –  Right “H”:   4 red arches, 2 yellow rectangular blocks.
  –  Grand Total:  13 blocks.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
2)  SELECTING MATCHING BLOCKS (BY INDEX)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

A)  LEFT TOWER  
  •  Orange Cylinders (#11) × 2  
    (Vertical cylinder as shown—no extra rotation needed.)  
  •  Orange Wedge (#15) × 1  
    (Matches the “roof” piece on top in the same orientation as the dictionary.)  
  •  Red Arch (#2) × 1  
    (Arch opening left‐to‐right, matching the main image’s orientation.)  
  •  Yellow Rectangular Block (#8) × 2  
    (Blocks oriented long‐side left‐to‐right, used as the mid‐level “platform.”)  
  •  Blue Cube (#5) × 1  

B)  RIGHT “H”  
  •  Red Arch (#2) × 4  
    (All four arches have their curved openings running left‐to‐right.)  
  •  Yellow Rectangular Block (#8) × 2  
    (Again, oriented with the long dimension left‐to‐right for the horizontal cross‐bar.)

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
3)  SUGGESTED ASSEMBLY ORDER
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

{
  Step1:  Move block with index 11   (1st orange cylinder for left tower base)
  Step2:  Move block with index 11   (2nd orange cylinder stacked above the first)
  Step3:  Move block with index 8    (1st yellow rectangle to form mid‐platform)
  Step4:  Move block with index 8    (2nd yellow rectangle completing mid‐platform)
  Step5:  Move block with index 2    (Red arch onto the yellow platform)
  Step6:  Move block with index 5    (Blue cube onto the front extension)
  Step7:  Move block with index 15   (Orange wedge on top of the tower)
  Step8:  Move block with index 2    (1st red arch for the right “H” base)
  Step9:  Move block with index 2    (2nd red arch for the right “H” base)
  Step10: Move block with index 8    (1st yellow rectangle as the cross‐bar)
  Step11: Move block with index 8    (2nd yellow rectangle beside it)
  Step12: Move block with index 2    (3rd red arch on top of the “H”)
  Step13: Move block with index 2    (4th red arch on top of the “H”)
}

That completes a no‐rotation match to the Target Image using the indicated block‐indices from the Dictionary.
